The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 PM awards for govt officers

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, March 3: The Centre has decided to introduce the Prime Ministers awards for excellence in public administration for officers of the central and state governments.

 The awards are envisaged to acknowledge the performance of civil servants, especially those from fields other than the Indian Police Service, which is already honoured with the Presidents gallantry medal.

 The list of areas, which may be considered for the award, includes implementation of innovative schemes/projects; introducing perceptible systematic changes for building institutions; making public delivery systems efficient and corruption-free; showing innovation and adaptation to meet stakeholders requirements; extraordinary performance during emergency like floods and earthquake; and setting high standards of services and continued improvement showing high leadership qualities and improving employee motivations.

 All officers of the central and state governments individually or in groups or organisations are eligible to be considered for the awards, which comprises of a medal, a scroll and a cash reward of Rs 100,000. In case of a group of officials, the total award-money will be Rs 500,000, subject to a maximum of Rs 100,000 per person. 




